    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello Cythonians.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to use cython to  use the [clone](https://linux.die.net/man/2/clone) package but there is some flags in this function that needs to define the `_GNU_SOURCE` such as: CLONE_NEWNET, CLONE_NEWNS, CLONE_NEWUTS and all other flags that needs of `CAP_SYS_ADMIN`. And I can't to use the `#define _GNU_SOURCE 1` in any kind of way that I tried. I already tried to put it into a `enum`, add it in a header file (`.h` file),  and add the option `define_macros` in the `setup.py` file but without success.\r\n\r\nSo the question is: There is some way to define it into the file? If I run this project in the root mode all works as expected, but just in the root mode.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you for all kind of help and may the force be with you.",
