            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just for curiosity, when I added this header the program still doesn't working without root mode. So, after some searches I found that I needed to use the `capabilities` command of Linux Kernel, and with this command set a` CAP_SYS_ADMIN` flag to the generated program. After that it worked. If you'll run a python script the python instance needs to have this flag, turned on.\r\n\r\nThere is a great post explaining about it, maybe it can be helpful as it was for my: https://blog.container-solutions.com/linux-capabilities-in-practice",
